dcterms:description: OSPREY is a comprehensive software tool for protein redesign, specifically aimed at improving bonding affinity through optimization using the BBK* algorithm.

dcterms:description: Protein benchmarks from the Bruce Donald Lab at Duke University are used for evaluating the performance of protein design algorithms.

dcterms:description: An expanded problem set for computational protein design that includes various configurations of mutable residues to test the performance of design algorithms.

dcterms:description: The d[g]-[M]-[p] problem sets represent a series of computational protein design problems characterized by specific configurations of mutable residues.

dcterms:title: 62 real protein benchmarks
